The paper presents a process for secure transmission of data, which falls under the category of cryptography and network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the generation of a one-time pad, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The process involves encoding and decoding of data, which can be related to computer networks, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) another possible category. The paper also mentions the transmission of video and audio streaming, which can be related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a library of basic keys, which can be related to computer engineering, making cs.CE (Computer Engineering) another possible category.
